<topic id='business_definition_nurse__level_one_.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Nurse (Level One) - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
      <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_nurse__level_one_">Nurse (Level One)</xref>
 is a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_care_professional">CARE PROFESSIONAL</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
         <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_nurse">NURSES</xref>
 trained within the United Kingdom may initially join the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_nursing_and_midwifery_council_register">Nursing and Midwifery Council Register</xref>
 as a 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_nurse__level_one_">Level One Nurse</xref>, also known as a 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_nurse__level_one_">Registered Nurse</xref>, after the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_nursing_and_midwifery_council">Nursing and Midwifery Council</xref>
 receives course completion details and declaration of good character from the Higher Education Institution where they qualified.        </p>
      <p>
This reflects a standard of proficiency considered necessary for safe and effective practice under Level 1 Nurses Sub-part 1 of the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_nursing_and_midwifery_council_register">Nursing and Midwifery Council Register</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
         <i>
Note: 
                  <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_nurse">NURSES</xref>
 trained within the European Union or Overseas can also join the 
                  <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                  keyref="business_definition_nursing_and_midwifery_council_register">Nursing and Midwifery Council Register</xref>
 as a 
                  <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                  keyref="business_definition_nurse__level_one_">Level One Nurse</xref>. See the 
                  <xref href="https://www.nmc.org.uk/" scope="external" format="html">Nursing and Midwifery Council website</xref>
 for the requirements.            </i>
      </p>
      <p>
Registration as a 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_nurse__level_one_">Level One Nurse</xref>
 (<xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_nurse__level_one_">Registered Nurse</xref>) will be in one of four fields of practice:        </p>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <div>
               <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                     keyref="business_definition_adult_nursing">Adult Nursing</xref>
            </div>
         </li>
         <li>
            <div>
               <xref outputclass="supportingInformation"
                     keyref="supporting_definition_mental_health_nursing">Mental Health Nursing</xref>
            </div>
         </li>
         <li>
            <div>
               <xref outputclass="supportingInformation"
                     keyref="supporting_definition_learning_disabilities_nursing">Learning Disabilities Nursing</xref>
            </div>
         </li>
         <li>
            <div>
               <xref outputclass="supportingInformation"
                     keyref="supporting_definition_children_s_nursing">Children's Nursing</xref>
               <p>.</p>
            </div>
         </li>
      </ol>
  </div>
